SIMPLE: inexpressible
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexpressible
<hw>In`ex*press"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not capable
of expression or utterance in language; ineffable; unspeakable;
indescribable; unutterable; <as>as, <ex>inexpressible</ex> grief or
pleasure</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inexpressible</xex> grandeur.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Blair.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In orbs⟦br⟧
Of circuit <qex>inexpressible</qex> they stood.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexpressibles</ent>⟦br⟧
